Prices for petrol and diesel were increased by 46%  in the local RTGS dollar currency to 4.97 Dollars and $4,87 respectively and on Tuesday this week another sharp increase of up to RTGS $7.97 Dollars and RTGS 7.88 were effected. This attracted panic and mayhem in major cities as commuters got stranded after transport fares were simultaneously increased but government sensed danger and reversed the price increase. Simon Muchemwa reports… --ChannelAfrica--